.TH CLIPX-HISTORY 1 "December 2024" "ClipX 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clipx-history \- view clipboard history
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clipx history
.RI [ \-\-limit
.IR N ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B clipx history
command displays clipboard history entries in reverse chronological order
(most recent first). Each entry shows a short ID, timestamp, and content preview.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-limit " N"
Maximum number of entries to display. Use 0 to display all entries.
Default is 10.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
View last 10 entries (default):
.nf
clipx history
.fi
.TP
View last 5 entries:
.nf
clipx history --limit 5
.fi
.TP
View all entries:
.nf
clipx history --limit 0
.fi
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
Each entry is displayed with:
.IP \(bu 2
Short ID (first 8 characters of the full ID)
.IP \(bu 2
Timestamp in local time (YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS)
.IP \(bu 2
Content preview (truncated to 60 characters if longer)
.IP \(bu 2
Separator line (---)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Failure
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR clipx (1),
.BR clipx-restore (1),
